   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1872_01_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Hamburg, 3rd Jan. 1872<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co.<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>Following on
                from my esteemed letter<lb/>of 28th of last month I today merely intend<lb/>to
                supply you, for settlement at your earliest <lb/>convenience, with the enclosed
                duplicate of the <lb/>bill of lading for <lb/>
            <figure>
               <figDesc>Company sign Louis Kniffler &amp; Co. LK+C in large letters in the upper half, centrally below that the letter B</figDesc>
            </figure> #[?] 273 1¢ cloth<lb/>sent via Liverpool on the steamer “Glaucus”.
                <lb/>For the New Year that has just begun<lb/>I offer you my best wishes; may it be
                <lb/>an auspicious one for extending + <lb/>strengthening our connection. <lb/>Yours
                most cordially<lb/>H. C. Bock<lb/>⟨Bill of lading⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1872_01_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1872_01_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1872_01_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_4.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p> [...]<lb/>26<lb/>[...]<lb/>72<lb/>FRANCAIS<lb/>
            <lb/>via Marseille<lb/>Messrs P. D. HAMBURG<lb/>F<lb/>3/1<lb/>72<lb/>N 5-6N
                1.<lb/>L. Kniffler &amp; Co. 2 TOUR-T 2<lb/>+[?] 5<lb/>
                JANV[?]<lb/>72<lb/>ERQUELINES<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>Japan<lb/>⟨1871<lb/>Hamburg 3rd
                Jan.<lb/>H. C. Bock<lb/>R[eceived] 26th Feb. <lb/>25th March⟩</p>
      </body>
